<SUMMARY>
A binary choice model in which the utility of each option is the sum of its observed mean reward and an exploration bonus that is inversely proportional to the square root of its sampling count. The bonus is scaled by the horizon (with no bonus when the horizon is 1) and weighted by a learnable exploration parameter gamma. The decision is made via a logistic function applying an inverse temperature beta and an overall bias term.
</SUMMARY>

